Joseph FIANNACCA, Appellant, v. BOOTH & CO., Inc., Appellee. No. 149. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Jan. 5, 1931. William S. Butler, of Brooklyn, N. Y. (James A. Gray, of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. E. C. Sherwood, of New York City (Clarence S. Zipp, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree [39 F.(2d) 639] affirmed.
